.TH APFEL 1 "2026-04-17" "apfel @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
apfel \- Apple Intelligence from the command line
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B apfel
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ prompt ]
.br
.B apfel
.B \-f
.I file
.RI [ options ]
.I prompt
.br
.B apfel
.B \-\-chat
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B apfel
.B \-\-stream
.RI [ options ]
.I prompt
.br
.B apfel
.B \-\-serve
.RI [ server-options ]
.br
.B apfel
.B tag
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B apfel
.B \-\-benchmark
.br
.B apfel
.B \-\-model-info
.br
.B apfel
.B \-\-update
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B apfel
is a command-line interface and OpenAI-compatible HTTP server for
Apple's on-device FoundationModels large language model. Inference
runs entirely on-device on Apple Silicon Macs that have Apple
Intelligence enabled. No data leaves the machine for inference.
.PP
.B apfel
has three modes:
.TP
.B unix tool
Send a single prompt from arguments or standard input and receive
the response on standard output. Pipe-friendly. Respects
.BR NO_COLOR (7),
isatty detection, and returns structured exit codes for scripting.
.TP
.B interactive chat
Run an interactive multi-turn conversation with readline editing,
history, and automatic context trimming.
.TP
.B HTTP server
Expose an OpenAI-compatible HTTP API on a loopback or public port,
suitable as a drop-in replacement for code written against
.I openai.OpenAI(base_url=...) .
.PP
The model's context window is approximately 4096 tokens. Requests
that exceed it are trimmed according to the active context strategy
or rejected with exit code 4 if the
.B strict
strategy is selected.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-file " " \fIpath\fR
Attach file content to the prompt. Repeatable; accepts multiple
files.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-system " " \fItext\fR
Set a system prompt. Applied once per session.
.TP
.BI \-\-system-file " path"
Read the system prompt from a file.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIformat\fR
Output format.
.I format
is
.B plain
(default) or
.BR json .
In
.B json
mode, a single JSON object with
.BR content ,
.BR usage ,
and
.B finish_reason
keys is written to stdout.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output such as banners and chat headers.
.TP
.B \-\-no-color
Disable ANSI color output. Equivalent to setting
.BR NO_COLOR .
.TP
.BI \-\-temperature " n"
Sampling temperature. Non-negative float, e.g.
.BR 0.7 .
A value of
.B 0
gives deterministic (greedy) output.
.TP
.BI \-\-top-p " n"
Nucleus (top-p) sampling threshold. Float in
.BR "(0, 1]" ,
e.g.
.BR 0.9 .
.TP
.BI \-\-seed " n"
Random seed for reproducible output. Positive integer.
.TP
.BI \-\-max-tokens " n"
Maximum number of tokens to generate in the response.
.TP
.BI \-\-mcp " path|url"
Attach a local or remote Model Context Protocol tool server.
Repeatable; attach multiple servers by repeating the flag. Local
servers are stdio subprocesses; remote servers are HTTP endpoints.
.TP
.BI \-\-mcp-token " token"
Bearer token for authenticating to a remote MCP server. Prefer the
.B APFEL_MCP_TOKEN
environment variable so the token does not appear in process lists.
.TP
.BI \-\-mcp-timeout " n"
MCP server timeout in seconds. Default
.BR 5 .
.TP
.B \-\-permissive
Use permissive content guardrails for the session. The default
guardrail profile enforces Apple's standard safety policies.
.TP
.BR \-\-retry " [" \fIn\fR ]
Enable retry with exponential backoff on transient errors. Defaults
to
.B 3
retries when the flag is given without a value.
.TP
.B \-\-model-info
Print the active model's capabilities and exit.
.TP
.B tag
Read text from standard input and classify it into tags using the
on-device content-tagging model. Honors
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output
for plain or JSON output.
.TP
.B \-\-benchmark
Run the internal performance benchmark suite.
.TP
.B \-\-update
Check for updates and, if available, upgrade via Homebrew.
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable verbose debug logging to standard error in every mode.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print usage information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the version string and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-release
Print detailed release and build information and exit.
.SH "CONTEXT OPTIONS"
.TP
.BI \-\-context-strategy " strategy"
Context-management strategy applied when the conversation approaches
the model's context window. One of
.BR newest-first " (default), "
.BR oldest-first ", "
.BR sliding-window ", "
.BR summarize ", or "
.BR strict
(error on overflow with exit code 4).
.TP
.BI \-\-context-max-turns " n"
Maximum number of history turns to retain. Only meaningful with
.BR sliding-window .
.TP
.BI \-\-context-output-reserve " n"
Tokens reserved for the model's output. Default
.BR 512 .
.TP
.B \-\-context-status
Print the current chat context fill after each turn.
.SH "SERVER OPTIONS"
.TP
.B \-\-serve
Start the OpenAI-compatible HTTP server.
.TP
.BI \-\-port " number"
Port to bind. Default
.BR 11434 .
.TP
.BI \-\-host " address"
Bind address. Default
.BR 127.0.0.1 .
Use
.B 0.0.0.0
to accept connections on all interfaces.
.TP
.B \-\-cors
Emit permissive CORS headers for browser clients.
.TP
.BI \-\-allowed-origins " origins"
Comma-separated list of additional origins to permit alongside the
localhost defaults.
.TP
.B \-\-no-origin-check
Disable the origin check entirely. Allows any origin. Dangerous on
non-loopback binds.
.TP
.BI \-\-token " secret"
Require a
.B Bearer
token on all requests except
.B /health
(see
.BR \-\-public-health ).
.TP
.B \-\-token-auto
Generate a random Bearer token, require it, and print it to stderr
once at startup.
.TP
.B \-\-public-health
Keep
.B /health
unauthenticated when a token is required. Useful for load balancers
and uptime checks on non-loopback binds.
.TP
.B \-\-footgun
Disable all protections. Equivalent to
.B \-\-no-origin-check
and
.BR \-\-cors .
Intended for local development only.
.TP
.BI \-\-max-concurrent " n"
Maximum number of concurrent model requests. Default
.BR 5 .
Additional requests are queued.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B APFEL_SYSTEM_PROMPT
Default system prompt for every invocation.
.TP
.B APFEL_MCP
Colon-separated list of MCP server paths or URLs to attach.
Equivalent to repeating
.BR \-\-mcp .
.TP
.B APFEL_MCP_TIMEOUT
MCP server timeout in seconds. Default
.BR 5 .
.TP
.B APFEL_MCP_TOKEN
Bearer token for authenticating to remote MCP servers. Preferred
over
.B \-\-mcp-token
so the token does not appear in process lists.
.TP
.B APFEL_HOST
Server bind address. Default
.BR 127.0.0.1 .
.TP
.B APFEL_PORT
Server port. Default
.BR 11434 .
.TP
.B APFEL_TOKEN
Bearer token for server authentication. Equivalent to
.BR \-\-token .
.TP
.B APFEL_TEMPERATURE
Default sampling temperature.
.TP
.B APFEL_MAX_TOKENS
Default maximum number of tokens to generate.
.TP
.B APFEL_CONTEXT_STRATEGY
Default context-management strategy.
.TP
.B APFEL_CONTEXT_MAX_TURNS
Maximum history turns for the
.B sliding-window
strategy.
.TP
.B APFEL_CONTEXT_OUTPUT_RESERVE
Tokens reserved for the model's output. Default
.BR 512 .
.TP
.B APFEL_DEBUG
When set to any non-empty value, enables debug logging (same as
.BR \-\-debug ).
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
When set to any non-empty value, disables ANSI color output. See
.UR https://no-color.org
https://no-color.org
.UE .
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime error, including tool execution errors and unexpected
failures.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error. Invalid flags, conflicting modes, or malformed values.
.TP
.B 3
Guardrail blocked. The input or output violated the active content
policy.
.TP
.B 4
Context overflow. The input exceeds the model's context window and
the active strategy was
.BR strict .
.TP
.B 5
Model unavailable. Apple Intelligence is not enabled or the on-device
model is not downloaded.
.TP
.B 6
Rate limited or busy. Exceeded
.BR \-\-max-concurrent ,
or a concurrent session lock is held.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/apfel
Binary installed by
.BR "make install" .
.TP
.I /usr/local/share/man/man1/apfel.1
This manual page.
.TP
.I $(brew --prefix)/bin/apfel
Binary installed by
.BR "brew install apfel" .
.TP
.I $(brew --prefix)/Cellar/apfel/<version>/homebrew.mxcl.apfel.plist
launchd plist used by the Homebrew service integration
.RB ( "brew services start apfel" ).
.SH EXAMPLES
Send a single prompt:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
apfel "What is the capital of Austria?"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Stream a haiku:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
apfel --stream "Write a haiku about code"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run an interactive session with a custom personality:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
apfel -s "You are a pirate" --chat
.fi
.RE
.PP
Pipe input from standard input:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
cat README.md | apfel "Summarize this"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Extract the response in JSON mode with
.BR jq (1):
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
apfel -o json "Translate to German: hello" | jq -r .content
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start the OpenAI-compatible server on port 3000 with CORS:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
apfel --serve --port 3000 --host 0.0.0.0 --cors
.fi
.RE
.PP
Attach an MCP calculator server and ask a math question:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
apfel --mcp mcp/calculator/server.py "What is 127 * 31?"
.fi
.RE
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at
.UR https://github.com/Arthur-Ficial/apfel/issues
https://github.com/Arthur-Ficial/apfel/issues
.UE .
.PP
Known limitations:
.IP \[bu] 2
Context window is approximately 4096 tokens. Longer histories are
trimmed or rejected per the active context strategy.
.IP \[bu]
Embeddings, image generation, and image input are not supported;
the OpenAI-compatible server returns
.B 501 Not Implemented
for those endpoints.
.IP \[bu]
Requires Apple Silicon, macOS 26 (Tahoe) or newer, and Apple
Intelligence enabled in System Settings.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR jq (1),
.BR curl (1),
.BR brew (1),
.BR man (1).
.PP
Project homepage and full documentation:
.UR https://github.com/Arthur-Ficial/apfel
https://github.com/Arthur-Ficial/apfel
.UE .
.SH AUTHORS
Franz Enzenhofer and contributors.
